WorkItem.Description:
I'm questioning the value I'm seeing for the enchant "Precision" on Boots.  Rawr is rating it the top dps enchant at 99.11 dps followed by haste with 51.04 and so on.  
 
I read that sometimes right clicking and refreshing an item in WowHead will correct odd items but when I tried that, I got this error message "[Arg_NullReferenceException]
Arguments: 
Debugging resource strings are unavailable. Often the key and arguments provide sufficient information to diagnose the problem. See http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=106663&Version=4.0.60310.0&File=mscorlib.dll&Key=Arg_NullReferenceException"  
I'm completely illiterate to this language and have no idea what any of that means or what information you may need but I hope this helps.  
 
Precision can't really be the top dps enchant for boots....
WorkItem.Summary: [Mage] Incorrect DPS Value for Precision Enchant

Comments.Message:
Enchants can't be refreshed like items, they are static.

Please read and follow the Posting Guidelines, we need your character file.

You are most likely really low on Hit and need the Hit to increase your DPS dramatically.
I've attached the saved character file.  Thank you.
Do you have any argument as to why it wouldn't be the top dps enchant? Hit after all is the strongest stat after int.
Good point Kavan.  At first glance, it just seemed Mastery or Haste or any of the others would be better for dps.  But, you are absolutely right.  /blush
